    {
      "step_id": "18d338af",
      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 2) SAR reasoning (why these features matter for hERG)\n- **Absence of a basic nitrogen** is a major negative predictor: many potent hERG blockers bind via **cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic interactions** with residues in the channel cavity (commonly involving aromatic residues like Tyr/Phe) and benefit from being **positively charged** at pH 7.4. A neutral compound can still block hERG, but it typically needs **strong hydrophobic/aromatic engagement** and/or high lipophilicity plus the right shape.\n- **No aromatic rings**: hERG blockers frequently exploit **\u03c0-stacking** interactions in the pore cavity. This scaffold is hydrophobic but largely **aliphatic**; it can provide hydrophobic contact but usually with **weaker, less directional** interactions than aromatics.\n- **Rigid, compact polycyclic shape**: Many high-risk blockers are **elongated** with a basic center and hydrophobes spaced to match the cavity. This molecule is more **compact and \u201cglobular\u201d**, which often reduces optimal occupancy of the hERG binding site (though there are exceptions).\n- **Polar functionality (lactone + alcohol + enone carbonyl)** increases polarity/H-bonding somewhat, which can reduce nonspecific hydrophobic binding to hERG compared with very lipophilic, cationic scaffolds.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:02:45.596678+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "62c5135e",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) Mechanistic basis (how it would interact with hERG)\nhERG blockade generally arises from **binding in the inner cavity** of the channel (accessed from the cytosol), stabilized by:\n- **Electrostatic/cation\u2013\u03c0** interactions (favored by protonated amines),\n- **Aromatic/hydrophobic** interactions with cavity residues,\n- A **shape/length** that fits and can be trapped by channel gating.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T20:02:45.596710+00:00"
    },
    {
