      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 5) Verification / uncertainty check (alternative explanations)\n- **Could it still block hERG?** Yes, at higher concentrations it might show **weak/moderate inhibition** driven by hydrophobic cavity binding, especially if the compound is quite lipophilic. However, without a basic center and without aromatic \u03c0-surfaces, **potent** blockade is less consistent with known hERG SAR.\n- **3D conformation caveat:** the rigid fused-ring system fixes a 3D shape; if that shape coincidentally complements the cavity volume, it could increase binding more than 2D heuristics suggest. That\u2019s the main uncertainty.",
